{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Extract all direct and transitive dependencies from manifests and include them in vulnerability checks.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is between manifest parsing, dependency graph resolution, and the module that prepares vulnerability-check inputs. A unit test of only the parser or resolver would miss dropped transitive nodes at module handoff.","test_description":"Run scanner dependency collection against fixture projects (`package.json`+lockfile, `requirements.txt`+resolved tree) and assert the emitted vulnerability-check input set contains every expected direct and transitive package/version pair exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Vulnerability query results must match exact manifest version ranges, not package name alone.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior depends on real vulnerability API range semantics and request encoding/contract details. A mocked API can falsely pass while production API interprets ranges differently.","test_description":"Against a real vulnerability database endpoint, query dependencies where only some versions in a package family are vulnerable; assert returned CVEs correspond only to the exact manifest ranges and exclude out-of-range versions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.58,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Sort findings by severity (Critical > High > Medium > Low) and then by CVSS within same severity.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic ordering logic inside one sorter/comparator boundary, with no required I/O or multi-module coupling to trigger the failure.","test_description":"Given an unsorted in-memory list of CVEs covering all severities and mixed CVSS scores, assert output order is severity-priority first and descending CVSS within each severity bucket.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.88,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Manifest update changes only the affected dependency version; all other entries remain unchanged.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failures typically come from parser/updater/serializer interaction (key reordering, accidental rewrites, cross-section edits), not a single pure function alone.","test_description":"Use real manifest files with multiple dependency sections; run update for one target dependency; compare before/after to assert only that dependency version changed and every other dependency entry/value is byte-for-byte or AST-equivalent unchanged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Auto-generated PR is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure boundary includes git operations plus real repository API behavior (branching, commit, PR creation, diff rendering). Mocking these can hide auth, permission, or API contract failures.","test_description":"Run scanner against a test repository with real VCS remote/API credentials; verify one PR is opened, title/body are populated, and the PR diff contains exactly one dependency version change with no unrelated file edits.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Major version bump detection correctly flags breaking change by semver.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is a pure semver comparison rule evaluation within one logic boundary; no external systems are needed to expose the failure.","test_description":"Table-test semver pairs (e.g., `1.9.4->2.0.0`, `0.9.0->1.0.0`, prerelease variants) and assert breaking-change detection is true only for major increments per project policy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"If breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and review flag is surfaced in scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure is at control-flow integration: semver decision must gate PR module invocation and propagate a review-needed signal in output. Unit-testing one function won’t validate both side effects together.","test_description":"Wire scanner orchestration with real decision/output modules and a spy/fake PR client; feed a vulnerability requiring a major bump; assert scanner output includes review-required flag and PR client was not invoked.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
